Green tea is said to be the healthiest drink ever besides
water. With its many nutrients and antioxidants, drinking Green tea
has many benefits for you and your body. Green tea originated from china and has now spread
throughout Asia. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>According to Healthline.com, here are some benefits to
drinking Green tea: Green tea makes you smarterGreen Tea contains caffeine just like coffee. But not only
does Green tea contain caffeine but also amino acid L-thiamine, which can cross
the blood-brain barrier. By doing this it increases dopamine and the production
of alpha waves in the brain making you work better which will make you smarter.
Green tea may lower your risk of certain cancers Oxidate damage contributes to the development of cancer;
antioxidants may protect that from happening. Green tea is packed with many
antioxidants which could help reduce the risk of certain cancers such as Breast
cancer, Prostate cancer and colorectal cancer. Green tea may lower your risk of Type 2 Diabetes Research has shown that Green tea can improve insulin
sensitivity and reduce blood sugar levels. In a specific study made in Japan, Green
tea drinkers had an 18% lower risk of becoming diabetic. Green Tea helps you lose weight Green tea can boost your metabolic rate and studies have
shown that green tea leads to decrease in body fat. Green tea may help you live longer With all the health benefits of drinking Green tea, and if
certain risks are decreased from your life and health, that automatically ensures
that you can live longer. Try to drink a lot more Green tea in your diet from today. For an added sweetness and flavour, you may add honey, mint
or lemon to your Green tea.